{"title_page": "Boku no Piko", "text_new": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Boku no Pico\n| image           = Bokunopico.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the ''Boku no Piko'' DVD\n| ja_kanji        = \u307c\u304f\u306e\u3074\u3053\n| ja_romaji       = Boku no Piko\n| genre           = [[Shotacon]], [[Yaoi]]\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = ova\n| title           = My Pico\n| director        = [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]]\n| producer        = Seiji Kaneko\n| writer          = Katsuhiko Takayama\n| music           = Ashimagi Ora\n| studio          = Natural High\n| released        = September 7, 2006\n| runtime         = 33 minutes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = ova\n| title           = Pico & Chico\n| director        = [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]]\n| producer        = Seiji Kaneko\n| writer          = Katsuhiko Takayama\n| music           = Shinrobi\n| studio          = Natural High\n| released        = April 19, 2007\n| runtime         = 38 minutes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = ova\n| title           = Pico: My Little Summer Story\n| director        = [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]]\n| producer        = Seiji Kaneko\n| writer          = Katsuhiko Takayama\n| music           = Ashiragi Ora\n| studio          = Natural High\n| released        = November 11, 2007\n| runtime         = 30 minutes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = ova\n| title           = Pico & CoCo & Chico\n| director        = [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]]\n| producer        = Seiji Kaneko\n| writer          = Katsuhiko Takayama\n| music           = T2\n| studio          = Natural High\n| released        = October 9, 2008\n| runtime         = 35 minutes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''Boku no Piko'''''|\u307c\u304f\u306e\u3074\u3053|Boku no Piko|lit. ''My Pico''}} is a Japanese series of [[shotacon]]  [[anime]] [[Original video animation|OVA]]s produced by Natural High. The producer has described it as \"the world's first shotacon anime\" and was made primarily to be marketed to and appeal to a male audience of [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[shotacon]]s.<ref name=walrus /> The series consists of three episodes and an edited version of the first episode''.'' The series spawned a one-shot [[manga]], a computer game and a music video album. Because of the high cost of producing anime, the characters and contents were intensively product-tested before production began.<ref name=walrus>{{cite web  | last = Michael  | first = Christopher  | title =Bocku no Pico \u2013 An Animated Discussion  | work= [[The Walrus]]  | date = May 2007  | url = http://www.walrusmagazine.com/articles/2007.05-boku-no-pico/ | accessdate = June 4, 2009 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012103114/http://www.walrusmagazine.com/articles/2007.05-boku-no-pico/ | archivedate= October 12, 2007 }}</ref>\n\nThe series gained a niche following in the [[Anglophone]] world after a viral video called \"Don't watch an Anime Called Boku\" was posted on [[YouTube]] circa 2010. In the video, a male viewer is heard describing the three episodes of the OVA and comparing the experience of watching them to [[Deal with the Devil|selling his soul to Lucifer]]. It has since evolved into an [[Internet meme]] and a [[copypasta]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Don't watch an Anime Called Boku |url=https://archive.org/details/youtube-JAc17N7Wgr0 |website=Internet Archive |accessdate=19 June 2019 |date=28 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nAnyways enough about child porn... you like Nagito Komaeda?\n\n==Characters==\nAll character design was done by Saigado.\n\n;Pico\n:{{Nihongo|Pico|\u3074\u3053|Piko}} \n:{{Voiced by|Mariko Sakou}}\n:A blonde-haired adolescent boy who works a part time job at his grandfather's bar in the summer. He's often shown swimming, usually naked or in a blue [[Speedo]]. He has worn girls' clothes ever since Tamotsu gave some to him as a gift. Later, feeling hurt that Tamotsu wouldn't define their relationship, he rebels by cutting his hair and running away from home, although later on they reconcile. The following summer, Pico meets Chico, who is swimming naked in a stream, while riding his bike. He soon becomes friends with Chico, who calls him \"Oniichan\" (big brother), and they form a romantic and sexual relationship. In his relationships with both Mokkun and Chico, he is the [[Seme and uke|uke]], though in the latter relationship this is somewhat reversible.\n;Tamotsu\n:{{Nihongo|Tamotsu|\u30bf\u30e2\u30c4}}, also known as Mokkun, is a [[white-collar worker]] and regular at Bebe.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://anime.sod.co.jp/Pico.html#chara |title=\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u30fb\u30aa\u30f3\u30fb\u30c7\u30de\u30f3\u30c9 |work=Anime on Demand |archive-date=2007-10-10 |others=The official character bio for Boku no Pico OVA was archived by the [[Wayback Machine]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071010082346/http://anime.sod.co.jp/chico.html}}</ref> He seduces Pico after mistaking him for a young girl, but continues the relationship after discovering Pico is in fact male. He later buys Pico a girl's outfit, complete with a ruby choker and panties, which he persuades Pico to wear despite his initial protests. He views Pico solely as a sexual object, though later shows true concern for Pico after he disappears. Although he eventually reconciles with Pico, he is absent in the second and third OVAs. In his relationship with Pico, he is the [[Seme and uke|seme]].\n;Ojiisan\n:{{Nihongo|Ojiisan|\u304a\u3058\u3044\u3055\u3093}} is Pico's grandfather who runs a large but usually empty bar by the beach named Bebe. When Tamotsu visits him for the summer, he has Pico help out as waiter, which involves wearing a frilly pink apron. He introduces Pico to Tamotsu and suggests they spend time together.\n;Chico\n:{{Nihongo|Chico|\u3061\u3053|Chiko}} \n:{{Voiced by|Aiko \u014ckubo}}\n:A [[brunette]] boy who lives with his older sister in a large house in a secluded forest area and develops a sexual relationship with Pico in the second episode. He is younger and less sexually experienced than Pico. He often plays in the outdoors nude and secretly watches Oneesan masturbate. In most cases, Chico is the [[Seme and uke|seme]], despite his age, though his relationship with Pico is somewhat reversible.\n;Oneesan\n:Oneesan (\u304a\u59c9\u3055\u3093) is Chico's older sister and legal guardian. Perhaps because of her caring for Chico, and her isolated home in the countryside, she appears sexually frustrated and masturbates regularly. After being caught masturbating by the boys through a crack in her bedroom ceiling, she becomes the indirect cause of their experimentation. She has a large collection of cosplay outfits and sex toys that Pico and Chico use without her permission. She later fondles herself away from the boys when she finds them sexually engaged upon returning home from the grocery store.\n;CoCo\n:Coco is a teenage boy with long, black hair who Pico and Chico meet in the third episode. It is subtly implied that Coco is actually a so-called \"city fairy\", due to some strange minor occurrences in his vicinity, though this is never explicitly confirmed. Coco soon has sexual relationships with both Pico and Chico. After inadvertently causing some friction in their relationship, Coco decides to distance himself from Pico and Chico, though they do reunite with him at Tokyo Tower and end up having a [[threesome]]. He is also the main [[Seme and uke|uke]] of the three, but this can be reversed.\n\n==Media==\n{{Expand section|date=October 2012}}\n\n===OVAs===\nThree [[original video animation]]s have been released. All three were directed by [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]] and produced by Natural High. The first, ''My Pico'', was released to DVD by [[Soft on Demand]] on September 7, 2006. The second, ''Pico & Chico'', followed on April 16, 2007.<ref name=\"OnDemand\" /> The third episode, ''Pico & CoCo & Chico'', was released on October 9, 2008.<ref name=\"Ep4\" />\n\nA box set containing the first two episodes and the soundtrack CD was released by Soft on Demand on April 19, 2007.<ref>{{citation | title = AV(\u30a2\u30c0\u30eb\u30c8\u30d3\u30c7\u30aa)\u306e\u7dcf\u5408\u30c7\u30d1\u30fc\u30c8 \u30bd\u30d5\u30c8\u30fb\u30aa\u30f3\u30fb\u30c7\u30de\u30f3\u30c9| accessdate = 2014-08-22| url = https://ec.sod.co.jp/ec/shop/f_main.jsp|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070722114202/https://ec.sod.co.jp/ec/shop/f_main.jsp|archivedate=2007-07-22 }}</ref> On November 11, 2007, the first OVA was re-edited with a different script and re-released under the title ''Pico: My Little Summer Story''. The edited version is the only one of the series to be considered appropriate for viewers under 18.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2007-09-17/pico-kujira-promotional-videos-posted |title=Pico Kijuri Promotional Videos Poster |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |date=2007-09-17 |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#ccf; width:3%;\"| #\n! style=\"background: #CCF\" | Title\n!  style=\"background:#ccf; width:15%;\"| Original Release\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = My Pico\n| TranslitTitle       = Boku no Piko\n| NativeTitle         = \u307c\u304f\u306e\u3074\u3053\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2006|9|7}}<ref name=\"OnDemand\">{{cite web|url=http://anime.sod.co.jp/chico.html |title=My Pico |publisher=Natural High |language=Japanese |accessdate=2008-12-14 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070307182443/http://anime.sod.co.jp/chico.html |archivedate=2007-03-07 }} Page as it appeared in 2007, by Archive.org</ref>\n| ShortSummary        = An effeminate boy named Pico works at his grandfather's cafe during the summer, hoping to make some friends. He soon meets a man named Tamotsu \"Mokkun\", who seduces him, believing him to be a girl. Later at Mokkun's house, Pico asks Mokkun what he thinks of him, but he doesn't respond. Pico runs away and cuts his hair. Mokkun searches for him, and the two reconcile at the end of the episode.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| Title               = Pico & Chico\n| TranslitTitle       = Piko to Chico\n| NativeTitle         = \u3074\u3053\u3068\u3061\u3053\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|4|19}}<ref name=\"OnDemand\" />\n| ShortSummary        = Pico finds a boy named Chico swimming nude in a stream, and the two become friends. Later at Chico's house, Chico takes Pico to his attic, where the two spy on Chico's sister [[masturbating]]. Pico then shows Chico that boys can also do this, and the two have sex.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = -\n| Title               = Pico: My Little Summer Story\n| TranslitTitle       = Pico: Boku no Chiisana Natsu Monogatari\n| NativeTitle         = pico ~\u307c\u304f\u306e\u5c0f\u3055\u306a\u590f\u7269\u8a9e~\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|11|11}}\n| ShortSummary        = An edited version of the first OVA, with content more suitable for viewers under 18.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 3\n| Title               = Pico & CoCo & Chico\n| TranslitTitle       = Piko & CoCo & Chico\n| NativeTitle         = \u3074\u3053\u00d7CoCo\u00d7\u3061\u3053\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2008|10|9}}<ref name=\"Ep4\">{{cite web |url=https://ec.sod.co.jp/ec/shop/f_main.jsp |title=\u3074\u3053\u00d7CoCo\u00d7\u3061\u3053 |publisher=Natural High |language=Japanese|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070722114202/https://ec.sod.co.jp/ec/shop/f_main.jsp |archivedate=2007-07-22 |accessdate=2008-12-14 }}</ref>\n| ShortSummary        = Pico and Chico meet a pretty, feminine-looking runaway named Coco who lives in a hideout underneath the subway. Pico slowly begins to fall in love with Coco, causing him to question his feelings for Chico. The situation becomes exacerbated when Pico catches Coco and Chico having relations one night. Eventually, they reconcile, having a threesome atop [[Tokyo Tower]].\n}}\n|}\n\n===Manga===\nA oneshot [[manga]], {{Nihongo|''Ame no Hi no Pico to Chico''|\u96e8\u306e\u65e5\u306e\u3074\u3053\u3068\u3061\u3053|lit. ''A Day of Rain for Pico and Chico''}}, was written by Aoi Madoka and published in the May 2007 issue of ''Hanaota''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pico.bz/top.html |title=\u3074\u3053WEB |publisher=Natural High |language=Japanese |accessdate=2008-12-14 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/67HDQ6XR0?url=http://www.pico.bz/top.html# |archive-date=2012-04-29 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Visual novel===\nOn April 6, 2008, it was confirmed on the producer's blog that a PC game, {{Nihongo|''Pico to Chico \u2014 Shota Idol no Oshigoto''|\u3074\u3053\u3068\u3061\u3053 \u30b7\u30e7\u30bf\u30a2\u30a4\u30c9\u30eb\u306e\u30aa\u30b7\u30b4\u30c8|Pikotochiko shotaaidoru no oshigoto}}, starring Pico and Chico, was being produced. The game was released by {{Nihongo|Tinkorbell|\u3066\u3043\u3093\u3053\u30fc\u3079\u308b|Tink\u014dberu}} on October 15, 2010.\n\n===Music video album ===\nA music video album, {{nihongo|''Boku no Piko PV Song Collection: Boku, Otoko no Ko dayo''|\u307c\u304f\u306e\u3074\u3053 PV Song Collection: \u301c\u307c\u304f\u3001\u7537\u306e\u5b50\u3060\u3088\u301c|lit. ''My Pico PV Song Collection: I'm a boy''}}, was released in Japan on July 9, 2009. It runs for 30 minutes and includes more than 8 music videos starring the characters from the OVAs. It also includes a karaoke option for each video.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pico.bz/top.html |title=\u3074\u3053WEB |publisher=Natural High |language=Japanese |accessdate=2009-05-24 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/67HDQ6XR0?url=http://www.pico.bz/top.html# |archive-date=2012-04-29 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061115025610/http://www.pico.bz/ Official Site] {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{ann|anime|6908}}\n\n[[Category:2006 anime OVAs]]\n[[Category:2007 anime OVAs]]\n[[Category:2008 anime OVAs]]\n[[Category:Anime with original screenplays]]\n[[Category:Hentai anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Internet memes]]\n[[Category:Cross-dressing in anime and manga]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Boku no Pico\n| image           = Bokunopico.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the ''Boku no Piko'' DVD\n| ja_kanji        = \u307c\u304f\u306e\u3074\u3053\n| ja_romaji       = Boku no Piko\n| genre           = [[Shotacon]], [[Yaoi]]\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = ova\n| title           = My Pico\n| director        = [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]]\n| producer        = Seiji Kaneko\n| writer          = Katsuhiko Takayama\n| music           = Ashimagi Ora\n| studio          = Natural High\n| released        = September 7, 2006\n| runtime         = 33 minutes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = ova\n| title           = Pico & Chico\n| director        = [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]]\n| producer        = Seiji Kaneko\n| writer          = Katsuhiko Takayama\n| music           = Shinrobi\n| studio          = Natural High\n| released        = April 19, 2007\n| runtime         = 38 minutes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = ova\n| title           = Pico: My Little Summer Story\n| director        = [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]]\n| producer        = Seiji Kaneko\n| writer          = Katsuhiko Takayama\n| music           = Ashiragi Ora\n| studio          = Natural High\n| released        = November 11, 2007\n| runtime         = 30 minutes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = ova\n| title           = Pico & CoCo & Chico\n| director        = [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]]\n| producer        = Seiji Kaneko\n| writer          = Katsuhiko Takayama\n| music           = T2\n| studio          = Natural High\n| released        = October 9, 2008\n| runtime         = 