ar in the summer. He's often shown swimming, usually naked or in a blue [[Speedo]]. He has worn girls' clothes ever since Tamotsu gave some to him as a gift. Later, feeling hurt that Tamotsu wouldn't define their relationship, he rebels by cutting his hair and running away from home, although later on they reconcile. The following summer, Pico meets Chico, who is swimming naked in a stream, while riding his bike. He soon becomes friends with Chico, who calls him \"Oniichan\" (big brother), and they form a romantic and sexual relationship. In his relationships with both Mokkun and Chico, he is the [[Seme and uke|uke]], though in the latter relationship this is somewhat reversible.\n;Tamotsu\n:{{Nihongo|Tamotsu|\u30bf\u30e2\u30c4}}, also known as Mokkun, is a [[white-collar worker]] and regular at Bebe.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://anime.sod.co.jp/Pico.html#chara |title=\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u30fb\u30aa\u30f3\u30fb\u30c7\u30de\u30f3\u30c9 |work=Anime on Demand |archive-date=2007-10-10 |others=The official character bio for Boku no Pico OVA was archived by the [[Wayback Machine]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071010082346/http://anime.sod.co.jp/chico.html}}</ref> He seduces Pico after mistaking him for a young girl, but continues the relationship after discovering Pico is in fact male. He later buys Pico a girl's outfit, complete with a ruby choker and panties, which he persuades Pico to wear despite his initial protests. He views Pico solely as a sexual object, though later shows true concern for Pico after he disappears. Although he eventually reconciles with Pico, he is absent in the second and third OVAs. In his relationship with Pico, he is the [[Seme and uke|seme]].\n;Ojiisan\n:{{Nihongo|Ojiisan|\u304a\u3058\u3044\u3055\u3093}} is Pico's grandfather who runs a large but usually empty bar by the beach named Bebe. When Tamotsu visits him for the summer, he has Pico help out as waiter, which involves wearing a frilly pink apron. He introduces Pico to Tamotsu and suggests they spend time together.\n;Chico\n:{{Nihongo|Chico|\u3061\u3053|Chiko}} \n:{{Voiced by|Aiko \u014ckubo}}\n:A [[brunette]] boy who lives with his older sister in a large house in a secluded forest area and develops a sexual relationship with Pico in the second episode. He is younger and less sexually experienced than Pico. He often plays in the outdoors nude and secretly watches Oneesan masturbate. In most cases, Chico is the [[Seme and uke|seme]], despite his age, though his relationship with Pico is somewhat reversible.\n;Oneesan\n:Oneesan (\u304a\u59c9\u3055\u3093) is Chico's older sister and legal guardian. Perhaps because of her caring for Chico, and her isolated home in the countryside, she appears sexually frustrated and masturbates regularly. After being caught masturbating by the boys through a crack in her bedroom ceiling, she becomes the indirect cause of their experimentation. She has a large collection of cosplay outfits and sex toys that Pico and Chico use without her permission. She later fondles herself away from the boys when she finds them sexually engaged upon returning home from the grocery store.\n;CoCo\n:Coco is a teenage boy with long, black hair who Pico and Chico meet in the third episode. It is subtly implied that Coco is actually a so-called \"city fairy\", due to some strange minor occurrences in his vicinity, though this is never explicitly confirmed. Coco soon has sexual relationships with both Pico and Chico. After inadvertently causing some friction in their relationship, Coco decides to distance himself from Pico and Chico, though they do reunite with him at Tokyo Tower and end up having a [[threesome]]. He is also the main [[Seme and uke|uke]] of the three, but this can be reversed.\n\n==Media==\n{{Expand section|date=October 2012}}\n\n===OVAs===\nThree [[original video animation]]s have been released. All three were directed by [[Katsuyoshi Yatabe]] and produced by Natural High. The first, ''My Pico'', was released to DVD by [[Soft on Demand]] on September 7, 2006. The second, ''Pico & Chico'', followed on April 16, 2007.<ref name=\"OnDemand\" /> The third episode, ''Pico & CoCo & Chico'', was released on October 9, 2008.<ref name=\"Ep4\" />\n\nA box set containing the first two episodes and the soundtrack CD was released by Soft on Demand on April 19, 2007.<ref>{{citation | title = AV(\u30a2\u30c0\u30eb\u30c8\u30d3\u30c7\u30aa)\u306e\u7dcf\u5408\u30c7\u30d1\u30fc\u30c8 \u30bd\u30d5\u30c8\u30fb\u30aa\u30f3\u30fb\u30c7\u30de\u30f3\u30c9| accessdate = 2014-08-22| url = https://ec.sod.co.jp/ec/shop/f_main.jsp|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070722114202/https://ec.sod.co.jp/ec/shop/f_main.jsp|archivedate=2007-07-22 }}</ref> On November 11, 2007, the first OVA was re-edited with a different script and re-released under the title ''Pico: My Little Summer Story''. The edited version is the only one of the series to be considered appropriate for viewers under 18.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2007-09-17/pico-kujira-promotional-videos-posted |title=Pico Kijuri Promotional Videos Poster |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |date=2007-09-17 |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#ccf; width:3%;\"| #\n! style=\"background: #CCF\" | Title\n!  style=\"background:#ccf; width:15%;\"| Original Release\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = My Pico\n| TranslitTitle       = Boku no Piko\n| NativeTitle         = \u307c\u304f\u306e\u3074\u3053\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2006|9|7}}<ref name=\"OnDemand\">{{cite web|url=http://anime.sod.co.jp/chico.html |title=My Pico |publisher=Natural High |language=Japanese |accessdate=2008-12-14 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070307182443/http://anime.sod.co.jp/chico.html |archivedate=2007-03-07 }} Page as it appeared in 2007, by Archive.org</ref>\n| ShortSummary        = 